---
import DocsLayout from '../../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import SyntaxCode from '../../../../components/SyntaxCode.astro';
---
<DocsLayout title="Tutorial: your first Kumo library" description="Build a Button and Field with a Kumo framework package.">
<p class="eyebrow">Tutorial</p><h1>Your first Kumo library</h1>
<p class="lede">Build the same small interaction in Vue, Svelte, or Solid. This tutorial uses the exact production artifacts exercised by the package receipts.</p>
<h2>1 — Choose a package</h2>
<SyntaxCode lang="shell" label="Terminal" code={`# Vue
npm install https://kumo-compiler.coey.dev/packages/kumo-vue-0.0.1.tgz

# Svelte
npm install https://kumo-compiler.coey.dev/packages/kumo-svelte-0.0.1.tgz

# Solid
npm install https://kumo-compiler.coey.dev/packages/kumo-solid-0.0.1.tgz`} />
<p>Use only one command in your project. npm installs the matching framework peer dependency if your app does not already provide it.</p>
<h2>2 — Import the library and its styles</h2>
<h3>Svelte</h3><SyntaxCode lang="svelte" label="App.svelte" code={`<script>
  import { Button, Field } from '@acoyfellow/kumo-svelte';
  import '@acoyfellow/kumo-svelte/styles.css';

  let clicks = $state(0);
  let project = $state('Workers');
</script>

<Button onclick={() => clicks += 1}>Clicked {clicks}</Button>
<Field
  id="project"
  label="Project"
  description="A production project name."
  required
  bind:value={project}
/>

<p>Model: {project}</p>`} />
<h3>Vue</h3><SyntaxCode lang="vue" label="App.vue" code={`<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';
import { Button, Field } from '@acoyfellow/kumo-vue';
import '@acoyfellow/kumo-vue/styles.css';

const clicks = ref(0);
const project = ref('Workers');
</script>

<template>
  <Button @click="clicks++">Clicked {{ clicks }}</Button>
  <Field id="project" label="Project" description="A production project name." required v-model="project" />
  <p>Model: {{ project }}</p>
</template>`} />
<h3>Solid</h3><SyntaxCode lang="tsx" label="App.tsx" code={`import { createSignal } from 'solid-js';
import { Button, Field } from '@acoyfellow/kumo-solid';
import '@acoyfellow/kumo-solid/styles.css';

export default function App() {
  const [clicks, setClicks] = createSignal(0);
  const [project, setProject] = createSignal('Workers');
  return <>
    <Button onClick={() => setClicks(value => value + 1)}>Clicked {clicks()}</Button>
    <Field id="project" label="Project" description="A production project name." required value={project()} onInput={event => setProject(event.currentTarget.value)} />
    <p>Model: {project()}</p>
  </>;
}`} />
<h2>3 — Check the contract</h2>
<ul><li>The button starts at <code>Clicked 0</code> and increments.</li><li>The label targets the input ID.</li><li>Description and error IDs are composed into <code>aria-describedby</code>.</li><li><code>required</code>, <code>disabled</code>, and <code>aria-invalid</code> reach native controls.</li><li>The package stylesheet supplies visible focus, state, spacing, and minimum 44px control height.</li></ul>
<h2>4 — Run the complete project</h2>
<p>Use the framework project rather than reconstructing files from this page.</p><div class="actions"><a class="action" href="/examples/">Open runnable examples</a><a class="action secondary" href="/docs/reference/packages/">Package reference</a></div>
<div class="note"><strong>Not included:</strong> Select and Tabs are absent from the package exports. Their evidence does not yet satisfy the package gates.</div>
</DocsLayout>
